    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>LIGHTNING</h1><p>The flashing of light. Lightning in the Bible often shows God&apos;s presence. It appears at important moments, such as:</p><ul><li><p>When God comes to Mount Sinai to give Moses the Ten Commandments (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:16\">Exodus 19:16</a>)</p></li><li><p>When describing Jesus&apos;s return (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:27\">Matthew 24:27</a>)</p></li><li><p>In visions of God (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:14\">Ezekiel 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:6\">Daniel 10:6</a>)</p></li></ul><p>The book of Revelation often uses lightning as a symbol. This book mainly aims to give a vision of God (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:5\">Revelation 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:5\">8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:18\">16:18</a>).</p><p>Lightning can represent different aspects of God:</p><ol><li><p>God&apos;s judgment against enemies (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:15\">2&nbsp;Samuel 22:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:18\">Revelation 16:18</a>)</p></li><li><p>God&apos;s power and rule over all creation (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:7\">Psalm 135:7</a>)</p></li></ol><p>In the book of Job, God mentions lightning to show Job how great creation is. This helps Job understand how small he is compared to God and creation (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:35\">Job 38:35</a>; compare <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:16-Ps77:18\">Psalm 77:16â€“18</a>).</p>",
